{#- TL;DR (body) — "In one paragraph". Two distinct paragraphs; #qbhire-in-brief-text
    (frozen speakable) lives on the first <p>. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbhire-tldr" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Hiring a ProAdvisor, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p id="qbhire-in-brief-text">Hiring a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor at TechBrot is a four-step, no-commitment path: a free file review, a written fixed-fee scope, a no-charge discovery call, then engagement start &mdash; you commit nothing until the scope and fee are agreed in writing. You can hire a ProAdvisor for five defined engagements &mdash; <a href="/quickbooks/cleanup/">cleanup</a>, <a href="/quickbooks/setup/">setup</a>, <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/">monthly bookkeeping</a>, <a href="/quickbooks/migration/">migration</a>, or <a href="/quickbooks/consulting/">consulting</a> &mdash; each scoped and priced separately as a fixed fee, never an open-ended hourly meter. Many businesses need a sequence rather than one engagement (cleanup, then bookkeeping; or setup, then consulting), and the free file review exists to name the right one for you.</p>
      <p>What &ldquo;independent ProAdvisor&rdquo; means for you is concrete. You keep ownership of your QuickBooks file and subscription &mdash; we work inside your company file under your own account, not behind our login, so ending the engagement never costs you your data. We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription &mdash; no Intuit affiliate revenue, no reseller commission &mdash; so plan advice reflects your business, not our margin. Published fee ranges (monthly bookkeeping $400&ndash;$2,500+/mo; cleanup $1,500&ndash;$15,000+; setup $750&ndash;$5,000+; consulting $500&ndash;$1,500/mo to $1,500&ndash;$3,500/mo) are estimates, not quotes &mdash; the exact fixed fee is set in writing after the free discovery call, and the full breakdown lives on the <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-cost/">ProAdvisor cost</a> page. We don&rsquo;t file taxes, represent you before the IRS, or perform audit or assurance; tax matters are coordinated with your CPA or EA. Independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PROCESS — the scoping path → process-grid. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbhire-process">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How it works</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Four steps to engagement &mdash; you commit nothing until step four.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">The scoping path is the same for every engagement type. The first two steps are free and carry no obligation; the fixed fee is agreed in writing before any work begins.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">{{ p.num }}</div><h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ p.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ENGAGEMENTS — five engagement types → r-3 dc-card. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbhire-engagements" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What you can hire for</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Five engagements &mdash; each scoped and priced on its own.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">You hire a ProAdvisor for a defined engagement, not a vague retainer. Each links to its own page for the full detail; the free file review names which one (or which sequence) fits your business.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for e in engagements %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ e.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ e.body | safe }}</p><p style="margin-top:10px;"><a href="{{ e.href }}">{{ e.cta | safe }} &rarr;</a></p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INDEPENDENT — what "independent" means → r-3 dc-card. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbhire-independent">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What &ldquo;independent&rdquo; means for you</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">You keep your file. We take no commission. We stay in our lane.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">&ldquo;Independent ProAdvisor&rdquo; isn&rsquo;t a slogan &mdash; it has three concrete consequences for the client.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for i in independent %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ i.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ i.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ROUTING — situation cards → r-3 hub-card. tel branch preserved. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbhire-routing" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Choosing the right engagement</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Which one do you need?</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:72ch;">Most businesses don&rsquo;t arrive certain which engagement they need &mdash; that&rsquo;s normal, and the free file review is built to answer it. Start from the situation that sounds like yours.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      {%- if b.href == "tel" %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="tel:{{ site.phone.e164 }}" data-tb-event="phone_click"><h3>{{ b.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ b.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- else %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><h3>{{ b.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ b.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- OPERATOR — how the engagement is run + trust-row. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbhire-operator">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How the engagement is run</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Written scope, your file, zero commission, CPA-coordinated.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Hiring a ProAdvisor at TechBrot is deliberately structured to protect the client. The fee is a written fixed fee agreed before work starts &mdash; an estimate at the file-review stage becomes a committed quote after the free discovery call &mdash; rather than an hourly meter you can&rsquo;t predict. The work happens inside your QuickBooks file under your own account, so your data and subscription stay yours throughout and after. We earn nothing from your QuickBooks subscription, so nothing in the advice is steered by commission. And we work strictly within QuickBooks and bookkeeping &mdash; we do not file taxes, represent you before the IRS, or perform audit or assurance work, coordinating with your CPA or EA where tax matters arise.</p>
      <p>The credentials behind the work &mdash; the active Intuit certifications and how the team is structured &mdash; are documented on the <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">ProAdvisor team</a> page rather than restated here, and our methodology and independence standards are on the <a href="/trust/">trust page</a>. This page is about how you engage; those pages are about who delivers and how we hold ourselves to it. Independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

